## Rule and Command File Paths

Rule (`.mdc`), command (`.md`), and skill (`SKILL.md`) files follow the same path rules:

| Type | Pantheon source path | Installed paths |
|---|---|---|
| Rule files | `.pantheon/.cursor/rules/*.mdc` | `.cursor/rules/<install-name>/*.mdc` |
| Command files | `.pantheon/.cursor/commands/*.md` | `.cursor/commands/<install-name>/*.md`, `.agent/commands/<install-name>/*.md` |
| Skill files | `.pantheon/.cursor/skills/*/SKILL.md` | `.cursor/skills/<install-name>/*/SKILL.md`, `.agent/skills/<install-name>/*/SKILL.md` |

## Notes

1. **Path check must be performed before each execution**: Do not assume paths; always verify each time
2. **Error handling**: If neither path has the script, report an error and stop execution
3. **Relative vs. absolute paths**: Recommend using paths relative to the project root
4. **Generated copies**: The target project may contain generated Pantheon copies under `.cursor/*/<install-name>/` and `.agent/*/<install-name>/`; do not edit them directly

## Error Troubleshooting

If you encounter a "file not found" error when executing a script, check:

1. Whether the correct path prefix (`.pantheon/` or no prefix) was used
2. Whether the `.pantheon/` folder exists
3. Whether `oracle` installed the generated copy into `.cursor` or `.agent`
4. Whether the script file actually exists at the expected path

### Recommended Diagnostic Commands (Does Not Rely on Search)

```bash
# Directly list the target directory (more reliable than searching)
ls -la ".pantheon/.cursor/scripts/jira" 2>/dev/null || true
ls -la ".cursor/scripts/jira" 2>/dev/null || true
ls -la ".cursor/scripts/prometheus/jira" 2>/dev/null || true
ls -la ".agent/scripts/prometheus/jira" 2>/dev/null || true

# Directly check if the file exists (most reliable)
test -f ".pantheon/.cursor/scripts/jira/read-jira-ticket.mjs" && echo "found: .pantheon" || true
test -f ".cursor/scripts/jira/read-jira-ticket.mjs" && echo "found: .cursor" || true
test -f ".cursor/scripts/prometheus/jira/read-jira-ticket.mjs" && echo "found: .cursor installed copy" || true
test -f ".agent/scripts/prometheus/jira/read-jira-ticket.mjs" && echo "found: .agent installed copy" || true
```
